<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-07-14T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-07-14T22:00:00-05:00" n="1158" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1158">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115B11/115</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-07-14T22:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 14, 1916, 10 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>209. Newspaper reports indicate <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi>
                            Government has taken possession of Babicora Ranch, Chihuahua, belonging
                            Babicora Development Company, American corporation.</p>
                        <p>Request to be informed immediately whether report correct. If so
                            immediately lodge protest and ask for release of property.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>